{
  "stem": "25639.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Joseph, Jozsi's nickname was Yechoshuah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then Michael's name was Mosche.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sandor's Hebrew name was Simcha.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Victor is Benjamin Wolf and mine is Channah, and my sister's Hebrew name is Shifra.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we had one synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was very crowded in it because even though we had only about 100 families, it-- we all had large families.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- but most of them were Hollenders.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So we-- we filled up the synagogue with Hollenders.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- I remember very warmly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember the name of the synagogue, but we didn't have the three-- the three branches of Judaism that we have in the United States.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So far as I know, all the synagogues were Orthodox in my region.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we celebrated all the holidays with the family together, and dinner, and the traditional foods.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The menfolk went to the synagogue, and-- and the women went also when they could, but mainly on the holidays.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had to stay home and prepare the food for the rest of the family, when they returned home from the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes, my brothers put on Tefillin in the morning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had to get up very early, and they took care of the animals, had breakfast, and then they went off to school or to work later.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was-- it seems like a hard life, however, it-- it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It-- we had a very warm and lovely family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think my brothers were so handsome.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We sang a lot in our family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I remember lots of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, after I survived the Holocaust, I had the need to write it-- write down the songs that my brothers had taught me and my sister.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
